  <description type="morphology">Plants aquatic, occasionally emergent. Rootstock nearly globose, 2-lobed. Leaves deciduous, bright green, pale brown toward base, spirally arranged, to 20 cm, pliant, abruptly tapering to fine tip. Velum covering less than 1/2 of sporangium. Sporangium wall ± brown-streaked. Megaspores white, 300--500 μm diam., rugulate to tuberculate; girdle obscure. Microspores brown in mass, 20--30 μm, spinulose. 2n = 22.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Spores mature late summer.</description>
